# Li World Studio & Li Engine

**Canonical:** `docs/game-dev/world-studio-vision.md`  
**Tracker:** `docs/game-dev/PH-world-studio-program.md`  
**RFCs:** `docs/game-dev/specs/`

## Syntax

- Use **`def`** for all new APIs in code and docs. Do not document bare **`proc`**.
- **`extern proc`** only for FFI/runtime stubs (C ABI), with full contracts.
- Parser may still accept legacy bare `proc` in old trees — reject that syntax in new Studio/game-dev docs and package code.
- Keep `requires` / `ensures` / `decreases` on every exported `def` and each `extern proc`.

## Product

- **One engine** for game + sim profiles — no CARLA/GROMACS/slicer forks.
- **Killer UX** (PH-UX): 60 fps, adaptive layouts, export wizards.
- **Agents:** MCP `li-engine` + `@cursor/sdk`; every path → `lic build`.
- **GPU:** CUDA + **ROCm/HIP** (no CUDA-only user kernels).
- **AM:** simulate + **export STL/3MF/G-code** to printers.
- **Drug design:** Lab-in-the-Loop + `studio.adaptive` + `li-chem` QM.
- **Publish:** `studio.publish` for paper-ready figures + repro bundles.
- **Compliance:** CRITICAL tier on `li-chem`, drug, AM export, `lic`.

## Do not

- Dump studio into `lic` compiler.
- Use `li-demo` for studio features by default.
- Add second physics engine for RL/sim.

## Phases

PH-GD (editor) → PH-SIM (profiles) → domain packs (ROBO, AM, SCI, DRUG) → PH-QM / PH-VOXEL / PH-PUB in parallel where deps allow.
